Adriene - I've followed you on several 30 day yoga journeys, and we have to talk about your choice of doing squats. 

Squats are unhealthy for those with knee problems - and as someone who's recovered from a knee injury, you should know that. 

You offer an alternative pose to almost everything except squats. I hate stopping my practice in the middle because my arthritic knees cannot not physically do a squat - and no, yoga blocks do not help. And dropping my heels is not the problem - it's the pain in my knees.

Please teach us another pose.

On my third back-to-back YwA journey. ðŸ’— This practice was exactly what I needed today. My confidence has been dented in two important areas of life, and yesterday I got knocked back again. This morning I needed to honor who I am and where I'm at, in the knowledge that being and divinity ultimately matter more than doing and achieving. Adriene has single-handedly inspired me to enjoy vinyasa yoga (I used to be all about the yin), and this practice surprised me with asanas that felt simultaneously familiar and new. The word "honor" also makes me think of a noble warrior, and the inner strength we all possess to persevere in the face of adversity

I have struggled with plantars fasciitis for years. It got so bad this year that I couldn't walk much, I wasn't sleeping and generally felt like garbage. In addition to physical therapy, I did your Yoga for the Feet video every day for months and other videos as I gained more mobility. Now after months of yoga and physical therapy, I can feel my feet and ankles are much stronger now. I can walk my dog again, I can sleep at night without waking up four or five times and I can start losing weight and living a more healthy life. Today, I am on day three of the yoga revolution. I was actually able to do the squat and lifting your arms in a prayer pose at 22:57 that I physically could not have done months ago, I almost cried. Through putting in the time, I have already been able in short time to transform my body. I am excited to continue the Yoga Revolution and see what other changes happen. Thank you for your videos Adriene, your sense of humor and your slower transition/easier to follow movements that helped give me the confidence to make the necessary changes to walk again and live life without pain! -Shelley

I wish I had one of those amazing stories that would say how incredible it was and that my child was inspired by the calm and sat next to me and attempted to mimic some of the poses. It wasn't at all like that.  There were some great moments and then there were moments where I had to pause the practice. But I did it from beginning to end with the help of your words of wisdom to honor this practice and accept where I am.  It certainly wasn't my best "yoga" but it was the most important "yoga".
